                            <html:h1 class="title">color QML Basic Type</html:h1>
                            <html:span class="subtitle"></html:span>
                            <!-- $$$color-description -->
                            <html:div class="descr">
                                <html:a name="details"></html:a>
                                <html:p>an ARGB color value. <html:a name="colorbasictypedocs"
                                    ></html:a> The <html:code>color</html:code> type refers to an
                                    ARGB color value. It can be specified in a number of
                                    ways:</html:p>
                                <html:ul>
                                    <html:li>By a <html:a
                                            href="http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/types.html#ColorKeywords"
                                            >SVG color name</html:a>, such as "red", "green" or
                                        "lightsteelblue".</html:li>
                                    <html:li>By a hexadecimal triplet or quad in the form
                                            <html:code>"#RRGGBB"</html:code> and
                                            <html:code>"#AARRGGBB"</html:code> respectively. For
                                        example, the color red corresponds to a triplet of
                                            <html:code>"#FF0000"</html:code> and a slightly
                                        transparent blue to a quad of
                                            <html:code>"#800000FF"</html:code>.</html:li>
                                    <html:li>Using the <html:a
                                            href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#rgba-method"
                                            >Qt.rgba()</html:a>, <html:a
                                            href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#hsla-method"
                                            >Qt.hsla()</html:a>, <html:a
                                            href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#darker-method"
                                            >Qt.darker()</html:a>, <html:a
                                            href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#lighter-method"
                                            >Qt.lighter()</html:a> or <html:a
                                            href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#tint-method"
                                            >Qt.tint()</html:a> functions.</html:li>
                                </html:ul>
                                <html:p>Example:</html:p>
                                <html:div float-right=""><html:p><html:img alt=""
                                            src="images/declarative-colors.png" /></html:p>
                                </html:div><html:pre class="qml"><html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-rectangle.html"
                                        >Rectangle</html:a></html:span> { <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>: <html:span class="string"
                                        >"steelblue"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">width</html:span>: <html:span
                                        class="number">40</html:span>; <html:span class="name"
                                        >height</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span> } <html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-rectangle.html"
                                        >Rectangle</html:a></html:span> { <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>: <html:span class="string"
                                        >"transparent"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">y</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span>; <html:span class="name">width</html:span>:
                                        <html:span class="number">40</html:span>; <html:span
                                        class="name">height</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span> } <html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-rectangle.html"
                                        >Rectangle</html:a></html:span> { <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>: <html:span class="string"
                                        >"#FF0000"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">y</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >80</html:span>; <html:span class="name">width</html:span>:
                                        <html:span class="number">40</html:span>; <html:span
                                        class="name">height</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span> } <html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-rectangle.html"
                                        >Rectangle</html:a></html:span> { <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>: <html:span class="string"
                                        >"#800000FF"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">y</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >120</html:span>; <html:span class="name">width</html:span>:
                                        <html:span class="number">40</html:span>; <html:span
                                        class="name">height</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span> } <html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-rectangle.html"
                                        >Rectangle</html:a></html:span> { <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>: <html:span class="string"
                                        >"#00000000"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="comment">// ARGB fully transparent</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">y</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >160</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">width</html:span>: <html:span
                                        class="number">40</html:span>; <html:span class="name"
                                        >height</html:span>: <html:span class="number"
                                        >40</html:span> }</html:pre>
                                <html:p>Additionally, a color type has <html:code>r</html:code>,
                                        <html:code>g</html:code>, <html:code>b</html:code> and
                                        <html:code>a</html:code> properties that refer to the red,
                                    green, blue and alpha values of the color,
                                    respectively:</html:p>
                                <html:pre class="qml"><html:span class="type"><html:a
                                            href="qml-qtquick-text.html">Text</html:a></html:span> {
                                        <html:span class="name">color</html:span>: <html:span
                                        class="string">"red"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="comment">// prints "1 0 0 1"</html:span>
                                    <html:span class="name">Component</html:span>.onCompleted:
                                        <html:span class="name">console</html:span>.<html:span
                                        class="name">log</html:span>(<html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>.<html:span class="name">r</html:span>,
                                        <html:span class="name">color</html:span>.<html:span
                                        class="name">g</html:span>, <html:span class="name"
                                        >color</html:span>.<html:span class="name">b</html:span>,
                                        <html:span class="name">color</html:span>.<html:span
                                        class="name">a</html:span>) }</html:pre>
                                <html:p>To test color values for equality, use the <html:a
                                        href="qtqml/qml-qtqml-qt.html#colorEqual-method"
                                        >Qt.colorEqual()</html:a> function. This allows colors to be
                                    accurately compared whether they are in property form or in any
                                    of the acceptable string specification forms.</html:p>
                                <html:p>When integrating with C++, note that any <html:a
                                        href="qtgui/qcolor.html">QColor</html:a> value <html:a
                                        href="qtqml/qtqml-cppintegration-data.html">passed into QML
                                        from C++</html:a> is automatically converted into a
                                        <html:code>color</html:code> value, and vice-versa.</html:p>
                                <html:p>This basic type is provided by the <html:a
                                        href="qtquick-module.html">QtQuick</html:a> import.</html:p>
                            </html:div>
